The paper deals with compressive sensing and model-based compressive sensing, which are primarily studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of the Constrained Earth Mover Distance (CEMD) model suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The development of novel approximation algorithms using graph optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
